},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e96ffb",
"children":[
"The diagnosis of BE is based on endoscopic tissue biopsy."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s4_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"a3d8b3",
"children":[
"Treat patients with BE without dysplasia with a ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"proton pump inhibitor",
"children":[
"PPI"
]
},
"."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"630dde",
"children":[
"Endoscopic ablation or mucosal resection is recommended for patients with confirmed low- or high-grade dysplasia."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s4_4",
"title":{
"__html":"Follow-up"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"b9c20d",
"children":[
"Follow-up"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"c9124c",
"children":[
"In patients with BE and no dysplasia, surveillance examinations should occur at intervals no more frequently than 3 to 5 years."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"0ecc85",
"children":[
"More frequent intervals of 12 months are indicated in patients with BE and low-grade dysplasia who do not choose endoscopic ablation."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"cdb14b",
"children":[
"Women with GERD do not require routine screening for BE."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"1f5c14",
"children":[
"Do not select antireflux surgery to prevent the progression of BE to adenocarcinoma."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
}
